ing%20energy%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETransmutex%2C%20a%20Swiss%20startup%2C%20is%20pioneering%20a%20new%20method%20for%20%26quot%3Bnuclear%20transmutation%26quot%3B%20that%20not%20only%20destroys%20nuclear%20waste%20but%20can%20also%20turn%20it%20back%20into%20energy%20%E2%80%94%20solving%20a%20key%20problem%20in%20nuclear%20energy%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20long%20considered%20nuclear%20energy%20one%20of%20the%20cleanest%20and%20most%20reliable%20forms%20of%20energy%20production.%20However%2C%20the%20waste%20it%20creates%20must%20be%20stored%20in%20deep%20geological%20repositories%20for%20thousands%20of%20years%20to%20prevent%20the%20environment%20from%20being%20exposed%20to%20harmful%20radiation.%20Transmutex%20says%20its%20technology%20can%20%26quot%3Btransmute%26quot%3B%2099%25%20of%20the%20world's%20high-level%20radioactive%20waste%20into%20new%20fuel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENagra%2C%20the%20Swiss%20agency%20that%20manages%20nuclear%20waste%2C%20validated%20the%20claim%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btheoretical%20possibility%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20company%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwitzerland%2C%20however%2C%20has%20pivoted%20away%20from%20nuclear%20energy%2C%20in%20part%20because%20of%20the%20safety%20concerns%20made%20apparent%20by%20Japan's%20Fukushima%20disaster%20in%202011.%20But%20such%20disasters%20are%20rare%20and%20many%20other%20countries%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0like%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20are%20betting%20on%20nuclear%20energy%20as%20the%20most%20efficient%20and%20sustainable%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20reach%20our%20goal%20of%20net%20zero%20by%202050%2C%20we%20have%20to%20at%20least%20triple%20our%20current%20nuclear%20capacity%2C%26quot%3B%20US%20Energy%20Secretary%20Jennifer%20Granholm%20said%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20companies%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20AI%20revolution%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-amazon-ai-nuclear-power-grid-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturning%20to%20nuclear%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20power%20their%20vast%20AI%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETransmutex%20CEO%20Franklin%20Servan-Schreiber%20believes%20the%20company%20can%20help%20these%20businesses%20go%20nuclear%20by%20destroying%20that%20long-term%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20know%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20waste%2C%20even%20if%20it%20takes%20a%20long%20time%2C%20we%20still%20know%20that%20in%20the%20future%20there%20is%20a%20limit%20to%20that%20waste%2C%20which%20is%20not%20gonna%20be%20a%20million%20years.%20That's%20the%20key%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2274dcc8b6-0d19-499a-83b1-07db6a1d5d37%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20new%20fuel%20cycle%20for%20nuclear%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223825%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Transmutex%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665a8ebe1cd3b177904254aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222053%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETransmutex's%20technology%20destroys%20nuclear%20waste%20and%20produces%20new%20nuclear%20fuel.%20%3Cp%3ETransmutex%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETransmutex's%20technology%20uses%20high-energy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphysics-atoms-empty-space-2016-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubatomic%20particles%20known%20as%20neutrons%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20destroy%20highly%20radioactive%20nuclear%20waste.%20While%20it%20can%20take%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%20for%20nuclear%20waste%20to%20decay%20to%20safe%20radiation%20levels%2C%20Transmutex%20says%20its%20technology%20can%20shorten%20that%20timeframe%20to%20just%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EServan-Schreiber%20says%20that%20over%20time%2C%20this%20system%20can%20also%20turn%20that%20waste%20into%20fuel%20that%20can%20be%20used%20again%20in%20nuclear%20power%20plants%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sort%20of%20nuclear%20recycling%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20you're%20able%20to%20burn%20waste%20and%20release%20energy%2C%20overall%20the%20process%20is%20very%20profitable%2C%26quot%3B%20Cameron%20Porter%2C%20a%20venture%20capitalist%20who%20manages%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.steelatlas.vc%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteel%20Atlas%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20an%20investor%20in%20Transmutex%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENuclear%20physicists%20say%20the%20company's%20technology%20avoids%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20concerns%20with%20nuclear%20energy%3A%20that%20the%20same%20fuel%20used%20to%20power%20nuclear%20plants%20can%20also%20be%20used%20to%20manufacture%20atomic%20weapons.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20that%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrei%20Afanasev%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20physics%20at%20George%20Washington%20University's%20Institute%20for%20Nuclear%20Studies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETransmutex%20avoids%20this%20risk%20because%20it%20doesn't%20produce%20plutonium%2C%20a%20key%20element%20for%20making%20nuclear%20bombs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20technology%20is%20also%20more%20efficient%2C%20Afanasev%20said.%20According%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Energy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fne%2Fnuclear-fuel-cycle%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSpent%2520nuclear%2520fuel%2520can%2520be%2Cof%2520operation%2520in%2520a%2520reactor.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espent%20nuclear%20fuel%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20still%20have%20about%2090%25%20of%20its%20potential%20energy%20even%20after%20five%E2%80%AFyears%20of%20operation%20in%20a%20reactor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20nuclear%20reactors%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20just%20throw%20away%20a%20big%20chunk%20of%20energy%20that%20you%20could%20use%20for%20everybody%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20this%20technology%20addresses%20this%20issue.%20They%20can%20extract%20more%20energy%20from%20the%20existing%20fuel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a5fab1a3-b2c5-49ef-90b5-c67ba57034aa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20firms%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20energy%20solutions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20industry%20is%20looking%20for%20new%2C%20more%20reliable%20power%20sources%20as%20the%20race%20to%20develop%20artificial%20intelligence%20ramps%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEnergy%2C%20not%20compute%2C%20will%20be%20the%20No.%201%20bottleneck%20to%20AI%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Di-o5YbNfmh0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20the%20Dwarkesh%20Podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20April%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20computational%20resources%20needed%20for%20training%20and%20running%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOklo%2C%20a%20startup%20backed%20by%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-nuclear-oklo-preparing-go-public-sam-altmans-spac-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetting%20on%20generating%20nuclear%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20small%20nuclear%20reactors.%20Its%20Aurora%20reactor%20can%20run%20on%20spent%20nuclear%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223149%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Franklin%20Servan-Schreiber%2C%20CEO%20of%20Transmutex%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666f6758ed9a404d829e3392%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222362%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFranklin%20Servan-Schreiber%2C%20CEO%20of%20Transmutex%2C%20believes%20the%20company%20has%20a%20new%20solution%20to%20long-term%20waste.%3Cp%3Enicolas%20lieber%20%2F%20photographie%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EServan-Schreiber%20said%20nuclear%20power%20might%20be%20the%20only%20way%20to%20support%20the%20industry's%20massive%20energy%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20requires%20massive%2C%20ind