A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6673640b087acd2be9b4efa5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22723%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon%20is%20trying%20to%20eliminate%20all%20plastic%20packaging%20from%20its%20fulfillment%20centers%20in%20North%20America.%3Cp%3ERobert%20Michael%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20said%20nearly%20all%20deliveries%20in%20North%20America%20no%20longer%20have%20plastic%20air%20pillows%20inside.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20change%20avoids%2015%20billion%20air%20pillows%20a%20year%2C%20Amazon's%20biggest%20plastic%20reduction%20effort%20yet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECompanies%20are%20under%20pressure%20to%20reduce%20single-use%20plastics%20that%20pollute%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20all%20Amazon%20deliveries%20in%20North%20America%20no%20longer%20include%20plastic%20air%20pillows%2C%20the%20e-commerce%20giant%20said%20on%20%3Cstrong%3ETK%20%5Bdate%5D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cs%3EThursday%3C%2Fs%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20said%20the%20change%20will%20avoid%20some%2015%20billion%20air%20pillows%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company's%20largest%20reduction%20in%20plastic%20packaging%20to%20date.%20Instead%2C%20Amazon%20is%20using%20a%20paper%20filler%20made%20from%20100%25%20recycled%20material%20that%20customers%20can%20recycle%20at%20home%20as%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20effort%20to%20eventually%20eliminate%20all%20plastic%20packaging%20from%20North%20American%20fulfillment%20centers.%20Amazon%20already%20met%20that%20goal%20in%20Europe%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20switch%20to%20recycled%20paper%20comes%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-global-plastic-pollution-treaty-under-scrutiny-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20and%20governments%20are%20under%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20phase%20out%20single-use%20plastics%20that%20are%20piling%20up%20in%20landfills%20and%20contributing%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20plastics%20are%20made%20from%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20can't%20be%20recycled%2C%20and%20degrade%20into%20tiny%20particles%20that%20leach%20into%20the%20air%20and%20environment.%20Scientists%20have%20found%20those%20microplastics%20in%20human%20blood%20along%20with%20organs%2C%20including%20the%20liver%2C%20heart%2C%20lungs%2C%20and%20most%20recently%2C%20testicles%2C%20but%20the%20effects%20on%20our%20health%20are%20still%20being%20studied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Oceana%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20advocates%20for%20protecting%20oceans%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazons-plastic-air-packets-boxes-circle-the-planet-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20criticized%20Amazon's%20ballooning%20plastic%3C%2Fa%3E%20footprint%20as%20the%20company%20shipped%20billions%20of%20packages%20around%20the%20world.%20Matt%20Littlejohn%2C%20Oceana's%20senior%20vice%20president%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20eliminating%20air%20pillows%20indicates%20Amazon%20is%20serious%20about%20its%20plastic%20reduction%20efforts%20in%20North%20America%20and%20welcome%20news%20for%20oceans.%20Plastic%20air%20pillows%20are%20made%20with%20a%20film%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dc38415b31a84dfb5aa56a438e162cc317827951d6b626391c4e894a25633a2fd%26postID%3D66736386b38735ca9df50ca4%26postSlug%3Damazon-cutting-single-use-plastic-shipping-packaging-paper-recycling-2024-6%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41893-021-00720-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat's%20commonly%20found%20littering%20marine%20areas%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOceana%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceana.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F18%2F2024%2F04%2FAmazons-United-States-of-Plastic-Oceana-Report-April-2024_reducedsize-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimated%20that%20Amazon%20generated%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%2094%2C000%20metric%20tons%20of%20plastic%20packaging%20waste%20in%20the%20US%20alone%20in%202022%2C%20a%209.6%25%20increase%20over%20the%20previous%20year.%20It's%20enough%20to%20circle%20the%20Earth%20more%20than%20200%20times%20in%20the%20form%20of%20air%20pillows%2C%20Oceana%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20disputes%20Oceana's%20figures%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsustainability.aboutamazon.com%2F2022-sustainability-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20a%20lower%20amount%20of%20plastic%20packaging%20across%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20global%20operations%20in%202022%3A%20Nearly%2086%2C000%20metric%20tons%2C%20an%2011.6%25%20decrease%20from%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOceana%20said%20its%20estimates%20are%20higher%20than%20Amazon's%20because%20the%20company%20doesn't%20account%20for%20orders%20sent%20by%20third-party%20sellers.%20Those%20independent%20sellers%20account%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsell.amazon.com%2Fsell%3Fld%3DSEUSSOAGOOG-sitelink-guide-D%26tag%3Dgooghydr-20%26hvadid%3D664128654868%26hvpos%3D%26hvexid%3D%26hvnetw%3Dg%26hvrand%3D11107216929719429337%26hvpone%3D%26hvptwo%3D%26hvqmt%3De%26hvdev%3Dc%26hvdvcmdl%3D%26hvlocint%3D%26hvlocphy%3D9007526%26hvtargid%3Dkwd-297084214751%26ref%3Dpd_sl_2vge9q2e84_b%26ld%3DSEUSSOAGOOG-BFBA12122B-CLK-D%26gclid%3DCj0KCQjw4MSzBhC8ARIsAPFOuyXwoFqkDpXAG0SpyouCS4LjcgY7qHDkeWaOK2XItdtbw5ohJv0188UaAtm2EALw_wcB%255C%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2060%25%20of%20Amazon's%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Amazon's%20plastic%20packaging%20data%20reflects%20orders%20shipped%20through%20its%20own%20fulfillment%20centers%20%E2%80%94%20which%20some%20independent%20sellers%20opt%20for%20%E2%80%94%20and%20through%20its%20grocery%20business.%20The%20data%20isn't%20broken%20down%20by%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20thing%20for%20us%20is%20to%20really%20test%20and%20learn%20and%20then%20scale%20what%20we%20can%20control%20within%20our%20own%20facilities%2C%26quot%3B%20Pat%20Linder%2C%20vice%20president%2